history.content:
<md>Hello! The Society of Women Engineers is looking for mentors for their High School Engineering Program (HSEP).

HSEP works to enrich high school students' understanding and range of experience with different engineering disciplines and inspire them to continue to pursue STEM in the future. The program is specifically geared towards uplifting female-identifying students interested in engineering, and we'd love to have you join! Come inspire an international group of curious students this semester and share your passion for engineering/CS :)

We're open to any and all folks interested in being a mentor! 
As a mentor, you'll help facilitate and design a project for a group of ~6 high school students over the course of 5 Saturdays starting on 10/17 to 11/21 from 11am-1pm PT. 

To learn more, visit https://swe.berkeley.edu/hsep
If interested or have any questions, please email swe.highschool.outreach@gmail.com or apply at http://bit.ly/hsepfa20mentorapp</md>
history.subject: High School Outreach Opportunity!
